==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peridotite
<hw>Per"i*do*tite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧ridotite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An eruptive
rock characterized by the presence of chrysolite (peridot). It also
usually contains pyroxene, enstatite, chromite, etc. It is often altered
to serpentine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The chief diamond deposits in South Africa occur in a
more or less altered peridotite.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peridrome</ent>⟦br⟧
